From 06a0c94e92bfa0e9a20f38d1f85865fd38437a76 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gautham Kumar Senthilkumaran <quic_gauthamk@quicinc.com>
Date: Fri, 21 Feb 2025 12:00:26 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd: Fix for primary link station
 association in OWE

Station sends association request for OWE with non-inheritance tag for
ignoring OWE diffie hellman paramter during the association request for MLD
link.

During this case, hostapd rejects the association request and notify the driver
to remove the station. But primary link have all necessary tag for association.

During the association of link sta, since it does not have the OWE pararmeter,
hostapd tries to remove the link sta from driver but driver does not have the
entry of the link sta, so it returns invalid during this case. Once driver
returns as invalid, hostapd tries to proceed with removal of MLD sta.

Fix this issue by not removing the MLD sta during association with AP and
reject only the link sta which does not have the OWE diffie hellman parameter
in its tag.

Signed-off-by: Gautham Kumar Senthilkumaran <quic_gauthamk@quicinc.com>
---
 src/ap/sta_info.c | 5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/ap/sta_info.c b/src/ap/sta_info.c
index ed7fe8b..74cbda7 100644
--- a/src/ap/sta_info.c
+++ b/src/ap/sta_info.c
@@ -230,9 +230,10 @@ void ap_free_sta_pasn(struct hostapd_data *hapd, struct sta_info *sta)
 static void __ap_free_sta(struct hostapd_data *hapd, struct sta_info *sta)
 {
 #ifdef CONFIG_IEEE80211BE
-	if (hostapd_sta_is_link_sta(hapd, sta) &&
-	    !hostapd_drv_link_sta_remove(hapd, sta->addr))
+	if (hostapd_sta_is_link_sta(hapd, sta)) {
+		hostapd_drv_link_sta_remove(hapd, sta->addr);
 		return;
+	}
 #endif /* CONFIG_IEEE80211BE */
 
 	hostapd_drv_sta_remove(hapd, sta->addr);
-- 
